Last updated: February 14, 2026

This application (“WACommerce”) is a testing and demonstration product created for development and evaluation purposes. It is not intended for production or commercial use.

1. Information We Collect

The App may temporarily collect the following information:

Basic account identifiers (e.g., username, email, user ID, or chat ID)

Device or session metadata (IP address, timestamps, logs)

Usage activity (actions performed within the app)

Data you intentionally submit while testing features

We do not intentionally collect sensitive personal information such as passwords for external services, banking details, or government IDs.

2. How We Use Data

Collected data is used only to:

Operate and debug the application

Test features and performance

Prevent abuse and diagnose errors

Improve functionality during development

This data is never sold and never used for advertising.

3. Data Storage

Because this is a test environment:

Data may be stored temporarily in logs or databases

Data may be reset or deleted at any time without notice

Backups may not be maintained

Service reliability is not guaranteed

Do not submit real personal or confidential information.

4. Data Sharing

We do not share your data with third parties except:

Hosting providers required to run the infrastructure

When required by law

To investigate abuse or attacks against the service

5. Data Retention

Data is retained only as long as necessary for testing.
We may periodically wipe all stored data.

6. Security

We implement reasonable safeguards for a development environment, but this is not a production-grade system.
Use at your own risk.
